    <description>A cross-platform GUI for youtube-dl made in Electron and node.js

### Features:

- Download from all kind of platforms: YouTube, vimeo, twitter and many more
- Download multiple videos/playlists/channels in one go
- Select the resolution and format you want to download in
- Download private videos (currently only tested on YouTube)
- Multithreaded, up to 32 videos can be downloaded synchronously
- Shows how much size the download will use up on your system
- The app automatically keeps ytdl up-to-date</description>
    <summary>A cross-platform GUI for youtube-dl made in Electron and node.js</summary>
    <releaseNotes>### **Changelog:**

**Features**
-  Use yt-dlp instead of youtube-dl (#[151](https://github.com/jely2002/youtube-dl-gui/issues/151))
-  Sponsorblock support (#[183](https://github.com/jely2002/youtube-dl-gui/issues/183))
- Add option to use empty user-agent string for downloading certain VR videos. (#[213](https://github.com/jely2002/youtube-dl-gui/issues/213))
-  No longer ship with binaries, download them on first launch

**Bugfixes**
- Ignore youtube-dl config file (#[190](https://github.com/jely2002/youtube-dl-gui/issues/190))
- Only set the default format if there are any (#[212](https://github.com/jely2002/youtube-dl-gui/issues/212), #[197](https://github.com/jely2002/youtube-dl-gui/issues/197))
- Fix chmod command on linux systems</releaseNotes>
